{"id":"342518584_Spatio-temporal_visual_analytics_a_vision_for_2020s","abstract":"Visual analytics is a research discipline that is based on acknowledging the power and the necessity of the human vision, understanding, and reasoning in data analysis and problem solving. Visual analytics develops methods, analytical workflows, and software tools for analysing data of various types, particularly, spatio-temporal data, which can describe the processes going on in the environment, society, and economy. We briefly overview the achievements of the visual analytics research concerning spatio-temporal data analysis and discuss the major open problems.","authors":["Natalia Andrienko","Gennady Andrienko"],"meta":["June 2020Journal of Spatial Information Science","DOI:10.5311/JOSIS.2020.20.661"],"references":["329869888_Steering_data_quality_with_visual_analytics_The_complexity_challenge","329411603_Augmenting_geovisual_analytics_of_social_media_data_with_heterogeneous_information_network_mining-Cognitive_plausibility_assessment","329100073_Semantics-Space-Time_Cube_A_Conceptual_Framework_for_Systematic_Analysis_of_Texts_in_Space_and_Time","329034274_A_conceptual_framework_for_studying_collective_reactions_to_events_in_location-based_social_media","326241623_Visualization_and_Visual_Analysis_of_Ensemble_Data_A_Survey","322976218_A_Survey_of_Methods_for_Explaining_Black_Box_Models","319629098_SensePlace3_a_geovisual_framework_to_analyze_place-time-attribute_information_in_social_media","318203022_Social_Media_Visual_Analytics","315527590_Visual_exploration_of_movement_and_event_data_with_interactive_time_masks","278724930_Geo-Located_Tweets_Enhancing_Mobility_Maps_and_Capturing_Cross-Border_Movement","276655299_Geovisual_Analytics_Approach_to_Exploring_Public_Political_Discourse_on_Twitter","261285923_Geo-social_Visual_Analytics","236675136_Scalable_Analysis_of_Movement_Data_for_Extracting_and_Exploring_Significant_Places","230753894_A_Taxonomy_of_Dirty_Time-Oriented_Data","220